## 3. Core New Table Definitions

### 3.1 Comments Table

```sql
-- ============================================
-- COMMENTS TABLE
-- Purpose: Post comments with nested reply support
-- Priority: P0
-- ============================================
CREATE TABLE comments (
  id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  post_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES posts(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id         UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  parent_id       UUID REFERENCES comments(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  content         TEXT NOT NULL,
  like_count      INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  reply_count     INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  is_hidden       BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  is_pinned       BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  hidden_reason   VARCHAR(100),
  hidden_by       UUID REFERENCES users(id),
  hidden_at       TIMESTAMP,
  created_at      TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at      TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Primary access patterns
CREATE INDEX idx_comments_post_id ON comments(post_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_comments_user_id ON comments(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_comments_parent_id ON comments(parent_id);

-- Feed queries: top-level comments for a post, ordered by time
CREATE INDEX idx_comments_post_toplevel ON comments(post_id, created_at DESC) 
  WHERE parent_id IS NULL AND is_hidden = FALSE;

-- Replies to a comment
CREATE INDEX idx_comments_replies ON comments(parent_id, created_at ASC) 
  WHERE parent_id IS NOT NULL AND is_hidden = FALSE;
```

**Design Notes:**
- `parent_id` enables nested replies (single level recommended for UX)
- `like_count` is denormalized for performance (updated via trigger)
- `is_hidden` supports moderation without deletion
- Partial indexes optimize the most common queries

